title: Grateful Dead Live at Baltimore Civic Center on 1980-05-04
description: Mississippi Half Step-> Franklin's Tower-> Feel Like A Stranger, Althea, El Paso, Easy To Love You, Brown Eyed Women-> It's All Over Now-> Don't Ease Me In-> Promised Land Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Solid Performance Great song selection and performances by all.  Sound quality limits this to a 3 star show, but the band has great energy throughout the first and second sets.  Excellent Ship of Fools with Jerry giving a heartfelt reading. Definately worth a listen.
sleeper? Listening to the Scarlet>Fire now, and band is on it.  Nice energy. Performance 5, sound 4

1st Show I don't remember much except that I was uber-wasted. Just listening to the show now for the 1st time since then and it's reallt got some good energy. Love the opening Half Step>Franklin's>Stranger and the Scarlet-Fire. Next show was Radio City Music Hall in the Fall and it's been a long strange trip since.
